      "message": "\u003e MSVC does not support a SSE4 specific flag: https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/en-en/library/7t5yh4fd.aspx\n\u003e I could go with AVX though, that would be safer as we don\u0027t have any of those optimizations. Fixing it.\n\u003e \n\u003e clang-cl does not seem to support clang\u0027s usual arguments (it\u0027s more like MSVC, cf https://clang.llvm.org/docs/UsersManual.html#id8). Also, in CMake, it is recognized as MSVC\n\nIf we could disambiguate then we could just do /arch:SSE4(_1?) for clang-cl, msvc would warn about an unknown flag. Did you want to downgrade to /AVX to try to limit the space between the two in case clang decides to emit something \u003eSSE4.",
